Vol / Page: 19
Edition:
Quote: The disease known to the Taupo and East Coast tribes as "ngere-ngere,"  to the Ngapuhi and Northern tribes as "puhipuhi" and to the Wanganui and  Western tribes as "tuwhenua," is oneand the same disease, and is true leprosy.
